d became firmly established at the time of the Reformation, although  <b>Nicolas</b>  is still occasionally found.  St Nicholas  was a 4th-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Nicholas Gainsford was born in 1386, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Nicholas Gainsford."},"et":{"<1386>–":"1386–Surnud","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1386–Male":"1386–Surnud","1425":"1425","about 1425":"umbes 1425","1386":"1386","1390":"1390","<1386>":"1386","Of,,, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hertford Co., Eng.":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"<1386>–":"1386–Kuollut","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1386–Male":"1386–Kuollut","1425":"1425","about 1425":"noin 1425","1386":"1386","1390":"1390","<1386>":"1386","Of,,, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hertford Co., Eng.":"Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"<1386>–":"1386–Décédé","1390–Female":"1390–Décédée","1425–Female":"1425–Décédée","1386–Male":"1386–Décédé","1425":"1425","about 1425":"environ 1425","1386":"1386","1390":"1390","<1386>":"1386","Of,,, England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hertford Co., Eng.":"Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Nicholas Gainsford est né en 1386, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fill